preference.name: TC_Fnd0Booleansolve_EffectivityIntegerRangeFromTo
preference.preference_description: 4th Generation Design can display effectivity ranges in one of two ways:Inclusive unit ranges, where the end value is included (a from/to paradigm). Objects whose effective unit range is displayed in a format such as Unit=1..10are effective for the end unit, in this case, 10. Set this preference to TRUE to use this display format.Half open ranges, where the end value is excluded (an effect in/effect out paradigm). Objects whose effective unit range is displayed in a format such as Unit=1..10 are not effective for the end unit. Set this preference to FALSE to use this display format. Valid Values: TRUE or FALSE.
